25|$|In 2009, Lundqvist {{became the}} Rangers {{spokesman}} <b>for</b> <b>the</b> <b>Garden</b> of Dreams Foundation, which works mostly with Madison Square Garden and its tenants to host charitable events and grant wishes to sick children, {{similar to the}} Make-A-Wish Foundation. In this role, Lundqvist hosts events and records public service messages. In order to benefit the charity, Lundqvist launched a clothing line, called the Crown Collection, on 19 January 2012. The items of the Crown Collection are available exclusively at retail outlets {{within the confines of}} Madison Square Garden.|$|E
