50|$|Walkden Gardens is {{a public}} green space in Sale, Greater Manchester. <b>The</b> <b>gardens</b> are named after Harry Walkden on whose death in 1949 his plant nursery passed to Sale Borough Council and {{provides}} <b>the</b> site <b>for</b> <b>the</b> <b>gardens.</b> <b>The</b> <b>gardens</b> are owned by Trafford Council and The Friends of Walkden Gardens help maintain and develop <b>the</b> <b>gardens.</b> A notable feature of <b>the</b> <b>gardens</b> is <b>the</b> dovecote moved there from {{the grounds of the}} now demolished Sale Old Hall.|$|R
